## Console Upgrades — where edits go (IMPORTANT)

The `agents/` console in this repo is a **rendered instance of the published
Marketing OS layer** (the `templates/agents/` scaffold in the open-source
`marketing-os` repo). It auto-upgrades via `marketing-os upgrade`, which
re-renders template-managed files with this store's config.

**The path for any change to the console/admin experience:**
1. Make the edit in the `marketing-os` repo under
   `packages/marketing-os/templates/agents/` (develop/prove it in the pooled
   `marketing-os-hosted-agents` twin first when practical).
2. Bump the `marketing-os` package version.
3. Run `marketing-os upgrade --yes` in THIS repo on a fresh branch → review
   the diff → PR.

**Never hand-edit template-managed files here** — the next upgrade will
overwrite them. Store-specific content lives in the protected paths (`docs/`,
`agents/brand/`, custom skills in `agents/src/mastra/skills/`, `.env`,
`marketing-os.config.json`) and survives upgrades.

## Brand Soul (agents/brand/)

`agents/brand/` holds this store's Brand Soul manifest — `brand.md` (strategy,
voice, guardrails; versioned + provenance-tagged), `DESIGN.md` (visual system),
plus the research brief and design-exploration prompts that produced them.
These files are **canonical** (D1: files are truth) and are injected into
every agent turn. Refinements happen in co-creative agent sessions and save as
new DB working versions; committing an approved version back to these files
goes through the normal PR pipeline. The public portal at `/brand/{slug}`
(+ `llms.txt` and raw files) publishes an outward-safe subset.
